DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260828
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260829
SUMMARY:Deadline: Instituto Sacatar: Sacatar Fellowship 2027 (Bahia\, Brazi
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Brazil's longest-running artist residency\, on the island of It
 aparica across the bay from Salvador\, hosting six to eight artists per se
 ssion for roughly eight weeks. Open to all creative disciplines and\, unus
 ually for this region\, to all nationalities\, which makes it one of the f
 ew genuinely international residencies in Latin America. Sacatar provides 
 full hosting (private room\, three meals daily\, individual studio\, laund
 ry\, local logistics and connections) but explicitly does NOT provide a st
 ipend\, airfare to Salvador\, art materials or discretionary local expense
 s\, so applicants must fund their own travel. Individual artists only\; gr
 oup proposals are not accepted and former Sacatar Fellows may not reapply.
  COVID vaccination is required. NOTE: there is a USD 25 application fee. A
 pply through SlideRoom by 28 August 2026. Contact info@sacatar.org.\n\nOrg
 anisation: Instituto Sacatar\nLocation: Itaparica island\, Bahia\, Brazil.
  Open to all nationalities.\nAward: Fully hosted residency: private bedroo
 m with attached bathroom\, three meals a day (except Saturday evenings\, S
 undays and Brazilian holidays)\, an individual studio suited to the discip
 line\, weekly laundry\, logistical support and airport transfer from Salva
 dor. NO STIPEND\, no airfare and no materials budget. USD 25 application f
 ee. One French artist may additionally receive airfare and a stipend throu
 gh Villa Fatumbi.\nDuration: Approximately eight weeks\; specific session 
 dates are listed in the application.\n\nMore: https://sacatar.org/en/fello
 wships/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://sacatar.org/en/fellowships/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantde
 sk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Itaparica island\, Bahia\, Brazil. Open to all nationalities.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:premio-klemm-artes-visuales-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T124442Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260904
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260905
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fundacion Klemm: 29th Premio Klemm a las Artes Visuales 2
 026
DESCRIPTION:The Premio Klemm is one of Argentina's longest-running visual a
 rts prizes\, now in its 29th edition\, awarded by the Fundacion Federico J
 orge Klemm in Buenos Aires. It is notable for a genuinely open definition 
 of medium: the entry categories explicitly include arte digital\, robotica
 \, video\, videoinstalacion\, audio and fotografia alongside painting\, dr
 awing and sculpture\, so technology-based practice is squarely in scope. E
 ntrants submit one work dated 2021 or later\, which must be durable rather
  than ephemeral. The top prizes are acquisition prizes\, so winning work e
 nters the foundation's collection. ELIGIBILITY IS RESTRICTED: Argentine na
 tionals (native or naturalised) or foreigners holding at least two years o
 f legal residence in Argentina\, aged 18 or over. Submissions close 4 Sept
 ember 2026 at 23:59. Prize amounts and the closing date are stated in the 
 bases y condiciones PDF linked from the entry site.\n\nOrganisation: Funda
 cion Federico Jorge Klemm\nLocation: Buenos Aires\, Argentina. Open to Arg
 entine nationals and to foreigners with at least two years of legal reside
 nce in Argentina.\nAward: First acquisition prize ARS 7\,000\,000 (around 
 USD 4\,800)\, second prize ARS 4\,000\,000 (around USD 2\,750). No entry f
 ee\; the foundation pays transport of selected works.\nDuration: Single pr
 ize with exhibition\; submitted work must be dated 2021 or later.\n\nMore:
  https://premioklemm.klemm.org.ar?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&ut
 m_medium=referral
URL:https://premioklemm.klemm.org.ar?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Buenos Aires\, Argentina. Open to Argentine nationals and to forei
 gners with at least two years of legal residence in Argentina.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fundacion-ama-amoedo-grants-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T124442Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260909
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260910
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fundacion Ama Amoedo Grants 2026 (4th edition)
DESCRIPTION:The Fundacion Ama Amoedo Grants provide resources and opportuni
 ties to strengthen the visual arts ecosystem and its institutions. Through
  an open call\, ten grants of USD 10\,000 are awarded annually across four
  categories: Artists\, Art and Social Engagement\, Organizations\, and Pub
 lications. The program supports the realization of projects by artists\, o
 rganizations\, and institutions with a meaningful connection to Latin Amer
 ica. This is the 4th edition of the grants\; the Foundation receives appli
 cations via its online platform from 7 July to 9 September 2026. ELIGIBILI
 TY: artists\, collectives\, art professionals\, non-profit organizations\,
  institutions\, and foundations with a significant connection to Latin Ame
 rica\, whether through nationality\, cultural heritage\, and/or the locati
 on where the project will take place. Refer to the Terms and Conditions do
 cument on the website for full details. Inquiries: info@fundacionamaamoedo
 .org. Application deadline: Wednesday 9 September 2026\, 11:59 pm.\n\nOrga
 nisation: Fundacion Ama Amoedo\nLocation: Open to applicants with a signif
 icant connection to Latin America\, through nationality\, cultural heritag
 e\, and/or the location where the project takes place.\nAward: Ten grants 
 of USD 10\,000 each\, awarded annually across four categories: Artists\, A
 rt and Social Engagement\, Organizations\, and Publications. No applicatio
 n fee mentioned.\nDuration: Applications accepted via the online platform 
 from 7 July to 9 September 2026.\n\nMore: https://www.fundacionamaamoedo.o
 rg/programas/becas?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referr
 al
URL:https://www.fundacionamaamoedo.org/programas/becas?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Open to applicants with a significant connection to Latin America\
 , through nationality\, cultural heritage\, and/or the location where the 
 project takes place.
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
